x4freetext: MP tandem accelerator
Munich Q3D spectrograph was used at ten angles
between 8 and 40 degr. The acceptance opening of the
spectrograph was 10.89 msr. The analysed products
were detected in a 1.8 m long focal plane detector
which made both deltaE-E particle identification and
position determination.
The target consisted of 118 mu-g/cm**2 120Te
deposited on a 16 mu-g/cm**2 carbon foil, and had a
certified isotopic enrichment of 99.8%
DWBA analysis was performed.
